Spark Indigenous Augmented Reality Creator Accelerator in partnership with @slowstudies_creative.

The five-week incubator program provides 10 Indigenous creators in Canada with customized, hands-on training to incorporate immersive augmented reality (AR) experiences as part of their cultural expression and storytelling. 

Emerging technology like AR, which overlays digital objects onto the physical world, allows creators to express themselves and showcase their culture in new ways, while connecting with audiences beyond the limits of physical spaces. Meta Spark currently enables more than 750 million people to experience AR for connection, communication and expression across Meta’s technologies every month.

My sketchbook cover design for @artsetobicoke Cover Story Exhibition for their 50th Year! There are 50 awesome designs to choose from. If you’re interested, you have until June 24th to add your bid. Link in stories and highlights.

By participating in this auction, you directly support Arts Etobicoke’s mission to provide equitable and inclusive access to arts and culture in West Toronto. 

Artist Statement: for little me…

Labels stick between my teeth as tight as threaded beads.
Thunder beings dance with glowing star, seed beads - like all of the constellations that have held me since before birth into this realm.
I come back to the multiple versions of myself that I’ve let go of many times before.
I now hold all of them as I dance with my ancestors and thunder beings, making little me so proud.

Materials: Duck canvas fabric, seed beads, thread, raw cotton canvas, pvc archival glue, acrylic paint.

Note: Start and end your sketchbook with a painting on the inside front and back of your new sketchbook - I added raw canvas!
 
My favourite part is the #GlowInTheDark Beads ✨

digging roots for skʌ:nʌ́ | peace

they rest their good mind on the land
for connection, love and healing
deep glowing roots extend from their hands
where new beginnings spark like the sun and the stars
much like the fire that burns in our hearts and spirits
we still carry flickers of hope for the future generations
weaving roots through standing stones
dancing with corn on rich soil
water embracing their back
trickling onto the earth below
to bring everyone home

@proofexperiences

The Waterfronts I Dream of

Underneath it all I wrote the words
You Are Loved
End the Millenium Scoop
For Gramma
For Mom and Her Siblings
Water Is Life
Ohne:kánus
Land Back

Dreaming of fresh flowing water falling from a hole in the sky
Where it spills through the hands of a celestial being of the earth
They’re holding so much love and care for everyone

A planet of rooted corn and a circle of floating fish 
They wondered where they could catch fish like this
And that’s exactly what it’s about
Food sovereignty, sustainability and body autonomy
For all generations

This is my heart
Open but protected
As I dream of gardening on the land again
Like when I was a little
Digging for fresh worms in the ditch
And putting them on hooks 
Even though I felt sad for them as they wiggled about
I did it for fresh pickerel and rainbow trout
For my family to fillet and fry

There are so many seeds for generations
That will sustain us through tough times
We are here now and we will be here in the future too.
